{
  "body": "Currently our [STYLEGUIDE.md](https://github.com/perl6/doc/blob/master/writing-docs/STYLEGUIDE.md) does not seem to mention that implementation-specific things generally should not be mentioned in the documentation. I think there are cases when such notes are somewhat allowed (e.g. see [dd](https://docs.perl6.org/programs/01-debugging#index-entry-dd)), but generally writers should avoid it by all means.\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/perl6/doc/issues/2054#issuecomment-391998003 for a bit more info.",
